1. PRIMARY SANSKRIT CORPUS (Devanāgarī / IAST source texts)
-----------------------------------------------------------
The corpus is built from digital-native scholarly editions, converted
mechanically (IAST/ITRANS → Devanāgarī) by this project's ingest scripts.

- Ṛgveda Saṃhitā (Maṇḍalas 1–10)
    Source: sanskritdocuments.org (ITRANS .itx masters).
    Terms: freely available for any use per sanskritdocuments.org.

- Atharvaveda Śaunaka; Pañcaviṃśa, Śatapatha & Aitareya Brāhmaṇas;
  Vājasaneyi & Taittirīya Saṃhitās
    Sources: GRETIL (Göttingen Register of Electronic Texts in Indian
    Languages, Universität Göttingen) and the TITUS project (Thesaurus
    Indogermanischer Text- und Sprachmaterialien, Universität Frankfurt).
    Terms: provided for scholarly, non-commercial use; copyright in the
    digital encodings remains with the respective editors/maintainers
    (e.g. Kümmel, Griffiths, Kobayashi, Gardner, Orlandi, Roth–Whitney).
    See gretil.sub.uni-goettingen.de and titus.uni-frankfurt.de.

