3. DICTIONARIES & REFERENCE WORKS (public domain)
-------------------------------------------------
- A Sanskrit–English Dictionary, Sir Monier Monier-Williams (1899).
    Public domain. Used for the concept store and query expansion.
- The Bṛhaddevatā, ed. A. A. Macdonell (1904).
    Public domain. Basis of the itihāsa/legend layer.
- R. T. H. Griffith translations of the Vedas (1896 and later).
    Public domain. Kept only as a cross-checking reference layer, not as
    corpus content.

4. MODELS & MAJOR SOFTWARE DEPENDENCIES
---------------------------------------
- Embeddings: sentence-transformers
